Adding to the other answers, you can use a DAO factory class that gives you access to all of the DAOs you need for one individual implementation class. This keeps code clean as you don&#39;t have to pass numerous DAOs to the constructor of your class. You only need to inject the single DAO factory. 

```
public class YourClassDAOFactoryImpl implements YourClassDAOFactory {
  @Override
  public CompanyDAO getCompanyDAO() {
    return new CompanyDAO();
  }

  @Override
  public EmployeeDAO getEmployeeDAO() {
    return new EmployeeDAO();  
  }
}
```

